  "question_html": "A length-scale (l) depends on the permittivity ($$\\varepsilon $$) of a dielectric material, Boltzmann constant (k<sub>B</sub>), the absolute temperature (T), the number per unit volume (n) of certain charged particles, and the charge (q) carried by each of the particles. Which of the following expression(s) for I is(are) dimensionally correct?",
  "options": [
    {
      "label": "a",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">A</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\">$$l = \\sqrt {\\left( {{{n{q^2}} \\over {\\varepsilon {k_b}T}}} \\right)} $$</div> "
    },
    {
      "label": "b",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">B</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\">$$l = \\sqrt {\\left( {{{\\varepsilon {k_b}T} \\over {n{q^2}}}} \\right)} $$</div> "
    },
    {
      "label": "c",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">C</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\">$$l = \\sqrt {\\left( {{{{q^2}} \\over {\\varepsilon {n^{2/3}}{k_B}T}}} \\right)} $$</div> "
    },
    {
      "label": "d",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">D</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\">$$l = \\sqrt {\\left( {{{{q^2}} \\over {\\varepsilon {n^{1/3}}{k_B}T}}} \\right)} $$</div> "
    }
  ],
  "answer": {
    "type": "mcq_multiple",
    "value": "bd"
  },
  "explanation_html": "$$[n] = [{L^{ - 3}}];[q] = [AT]$$<br><br>$$[\\varepsilon ] = [{M^{ - 1}}{L^{ - 3}}{A^2}{T^4}]$$<br><br>$$[T] = [L]$$<br><br>$$[l] = [L]$$<br><br>$$[{k_B}] = [{M^1}{L^2}{T^{ - 2}}{K^{ - 1}}]$$<br><br>(a) RHS<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {{{[{L^{ - 3}}{A^2}{T^2}]} \\over {[{M^{ - 1}}{L^{ - 3}}{T^4}{A^2}][{M^1}{L^2}{T^{ - 2}}{K^{ - 1}}][K]}}} $$<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {{{[{L^{ - 3}}{A^2}{T^2}]} \\over {[{L^{ - 1}}{A^2}{T^2}]}}}  = \\sqrt {[{L^{ - 2}}]}  = [{L^{ - 1}}]$$ Wrong<br><br>(b) RHS<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {{{[{M^{ - 1}}{L^{ - 3}}{T^4}{A^2}][{M^1}{L^2}{T^{ - 2}}{K^{ - 1}}][K]} \\over {[{L^{ - 3}}{A^2}{T^2}]}}} $$<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {{{[{L^{ - 1}}{A^2}{T^2}]} \\over {[{L^{ - 3}}{A^2}{T^2}]}}}  = L$$ Correct<br><br>(c) RHS<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {{{[{A^2}{T^2}]} \\over {[{M^{ - 1}}{L^{ - 3}}{T^4}{A^2}][{L^{ - 2}}][{M^1}{L^2}{T^{ - 2}}{K^{ - 1}}][K]}}} $$<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {[{L^3}]} $$ Wrong<br><br>(d) RHS<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {{{[{A^2}{T^2}]} \\over {[{M^{ - 1}}{L^{ - 3}}{T^4}{A^2}][{L^{ - 1}}][{M^1}{L^2}{T^{ - 2}}{K^{ - 1}}][K]}}} $$<br><br>$$ = \\sqrt {{{[{A^2}{T^2}]} \\over {[{L^{ - 2}}{T^2}{A^2}]}}}  = [L]$$ Correct"
}